        "content": "<p>is there some sort of enriched notion generalizing that of a modular lattice? i've seen the law μ(A) + μ(B) = μ(A ∪ B) + μ(A ∩ B) referred to as \"modularity\" by at least one source, and it seems an awful lot like this is in reference to modular lattices</p>",
        "id": 218032296,
        "sender_full_name": "sarahzrf",
        "timestamp": 1606418284
    },
    {
